[Mon 2026-04-20 11:39 PDT] Add a "Security Immune System" feature to WinSentinel with a `--immune` CLI command. This is a .NET 8 C# project.

## What to build

A service that acts like an immune system for the machine - it remembers past security threats (findings) and builds "antibodies" (defensive patterns) that detect similar threats faster in the future. It tracks vaccination records showing what the system has been immunized against.

## Files to create/modify

### 1. Create `src/WinSentinel.Core/Services/SecurityImmuneSystem.cs`

A service class following the same pattern as `ScoreForecaster.cs` and other services in that folder. Key features:

```csharp
namespace WinSentinel.Core.Services;
using WinSentinel.Core.Models;

public class SecurityImmuneSystem
{
    // Record types for results
    public record Antibody(string Id, string Pattern, string Category, string Severity, 
        int ExposureCount, DateTimeOffset FirstSeen, DateTimeOffset LastSeen, 
        string Status, double ConfidenceScore);

    public record VaccinationRecord(string ThreatCategory, int AntibodyCount, 
        double CoveragePercent, string ImmunityLevel, DateTimeOffset LastBooster);

    public record ThreatMemory(string FindingTitle, string Module, string Severity,
        int RecurrenceCount, bool IsImmunized, string RecommendedAction);

    public record ImmuneHealthReport(
        int TotalAntibodies, int ActiveAntibodies, int WeakenedAntibodies,
        double OverallImmunityScore, List<VaccinationRecord> Vaccinations,
        List<ThreatMemory> RecentThreats, List<string> VulnerableAreas,
        List<string> ProactiveRecommendations);

    // Main methods:
    // BuildImmuneProfile(List<AuditRun> history) -> ImmuneHealthReport
    //   - Analyzes all past findings across runs
    //   - Groups by category/pattern to build antibodies
    //   - Calculates immunity coverage per threat category
    //   - Identifies weakened immunity (threats not seen recently may lose immunity)
    //   - Identifies vulnerable areas (no antibodies exist)
    //   - Generates proactive recommendations ("Your immunity to X is weakening, run a targeted scan")

    // GetAntibodies(List<AuditRun> history) -> List<Antibody>
    //   - Extract defensive patterns from resolved findings
    //   - Confidence based on how many times threat was seen and resolved

    // GetVaccinations(List<Antibody> antibodies) -> List<VaccinationRecord>
    //   - Group antibodies by category
    //   - Calculate coverage percentage
    //   - Immunity levels: "Full", "Partial", "Weakened", "None"
    //   - Weakened if last exposure was >90 days ago

    // GetThreatMemory(List<AuditRun> history) -> List<ThreatMemory>
    //   - Track which findings recur across runs
    //   - Mark as immunized if the finding was resolved and hasn't returned
    //   - Recommend actions for recurring threats

    // IdentifyVulnerableAreas(List<VaccinationRecord> vaccinations, List<string> allModules) -> List<string>
    //   - Find modules/categories with no or weak immunity

    // GenerateRecommendations(ImmuneHealthReport report) -> List<string>
    //   - "Immunity to [X] weakening - consider targeted scan"
    //   - "New threat variant detected in [module] - booster recommended"  
    //   - "[N] antibodies expired - system vulnerability increasing"
    //   - "Strong immunity across [N] categories - maintaining good hygiene"
}
```

The `AuditRun` model is defined in `src/WinSentinel.Core/Models/AuditRun.cs`. Look at it to understand the structure. It has properties like `Findings` (list of `Finding`), `Timestamp`, `OverallScore`, etc. The `Finding` model has `Title`, `Category`, `Severity`, `ModuleName`, `Status`, `Recommendation`, etc.

### 2. Create `src/WinSentinel.Cli/ConsoleFormatter.Immune.cs`

Follow the pattern of other ConsoleFormatter partial class files (e.g., `ConsoleFormatter.Patrol.cs`, `ConsoleFormatter.Radar.cs`). Implement:

```csharp
namespace WinSentinel.Cli;

public static partial class ConsoleFormatter
{
    public static void PrintImmuneReport(SecurityImmuneSystem.ImmuneHealthReport report, CliOptions options)
    {
        // ASCII art immune system visualization
        // Show overall immunity score as a gauge/bar
        // Vaccination card table: Category | Antibodies | Coverage | Immunity Level | Last Booster
        // Threat memory table: Finding | Module | Recurrence | Immunized? | Action
        // Vulnerable areas list
        // Proactive recommendations
        // Support --json output via options.Json
    }
}
```

### 3. Modify `src/WinSentinel.Cli/CliParser.cs`

- Add `Immune` to the `CliCommand` enum (before `Help`)
- Add `ImmuneFormat` string property to `CliOptions` (default "text")
- Add `ImmuneDays` int property to `CliOptions` (default 90)
- Add `ImmuneShowExpired` bool property
- Add parsing for `"--immune"` or `"immune"` command in the Parse method
- Add `--immune-days`, `--immune-format`, `--immune-show-expired` flag parsing
- Add help text for the immune command

### 4. Modify `src/WinSentinel.Cli/Program.cs`

Add a case for `CliCommand.Immune` in the main switch statement. Follow the exact pattern used by other commands (e.g., Patrol, Radar, Forecast). Look at how they:
- Load audit history
- Call the service
- Call the formatter
- Handle JSON output

## Important patterns to follow

- Look at how `ScoreForecaster`, `SecurityAdvisor`, or `AnomalyWatchdogService` are structured
- The CLI commands load history via `AuditHistoryService` - look at how existing commands do it in Program.cs
- Use the same Console color helpers used elsewhere (like `ConsoleFormatter.WriteHeader`, color constants, etc.)
- All services are static or have static methods - no DI container
- The project uses .NET 8 with nullable reference types enabled

## Build verification

After making all changes, run:
```
dotnet build src/WinSentinel.Cli/WinSentinel.Cli.csproj --no-restore -q
```

If that fails, fix the errors. Do NOT leave broken code.

Also check:
```
dotnet build src/WinSentinel.Core/WinSentinel.Core.csproj --no-restore -q
```

## Git

After verifying the build passes, commit with message:
```
feat: add Security Immune System (--immune) - adaptive threat memory with vaccination records, antibodies, and proactive immunity recommendations
```

Do NOT push - I will push after reviewing.
